<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <head>
        <title>flexbox</title>
        <style>
            .parent{
                width: 100%;
                height: 100vh;
                display: flex;
                justify-content: flex-start;

            }
            .child{
                height: 200px;
                width: 200px;
                border: 1px solid black;
                color: white;
                flex-basis: 2;
            }
            .c1{
                background-color: red;
                
            }
            .c2{
                background-color: blue;
              
            }
            .c3{
                background-color: green;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="parent">
            <div class="child c1">1</div>
            <div class="child c2">2</div>
            <div class="child c3">3</div>

        </div>
    </body>
</html>


//24/02/2025

flex-box 

it is short form 

display:flex;

justify-content: flex-start, flex-end, space-evenly, space-between, space-around

align-items: flex-start, flex-end, center, stretch

gap- it defines the gap between the html elements 

Ex: gap:20px;

flex-direction: row, column, row-reverse, column-reverse

order - it specifies the order of html elements

flex-grow - it defines the expansion proportion of particular element by default is 0

flex-shrink - it defines the collapsion/compression
default value is 1

flex-basis - it defines the initial size of the element
